The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Calcutta: The Indian Premier League (IPL) Tuesday announced that the Deccan Chargers will host two of their matches in Cuttack, which would now serve as a home venue of the Hyderabad franchise with a view to catering to the catchment area of the fans of the reigning champions. The move follows a series of discussions and a request from the Chargers to host matches close to their home base, stated a release.     
	Revised Chargers schedule: Mar. 12: Vs Kolkata Knight Riders (Mumbai); Mar. 19: Vs Kings XI Punjab (Cuttack); Mar. 21: Vs Delhi DareDevils (Cuttack); Mar. 28: Vs Mumbai Indians (Mumbai); April 5: Vs Rajasthan Royals (Nagpur); April 10: Vs Chennai Super Kings (Nagpur); April 12: Vs Royal Challengers Bangalore (Nagpur).        
	New Delhi: Decision making in the IPL smacks of arrogance and the T20 format is ripe for corruption, believes Federation of International Cricketers Associations CEO Tim May. May referred to the league authorities refusal to share security plans with the foreign cricketers to make his point.          
	Cuttack: Orissa defeated Assam by 51 runs Tuesday to set up a zonal summit clash with Bengal in the East Zone Vijay Hazare Trophy while half-centuries by Ishan Jaggi and Rajiv Kumar helped Jharkhand beat Tripura by two wickets.    
	SUMMARISED SCORES    
	Orissa 288/8 (P. Patel 78, R. Mohanty 73; S. Bahutule 3/52). Assam 237 (P. Aziz 62; R. Mohanty 3/38, B. Samantray 3/24). Orissa won by 51 runs l Tripura 241/8 (B. Das n.o. 61). Jharkhand 245/8 (R. Kumar 55; M. Murasingh 1/2). Jharkhand won by 2 wickets.         
	Melbourne: Australia Tuesday decided to rest Michael Hussey and Nathan Hauritz for Fridays final one-dayer of the ODI series against the West Indies which the hosts have already clinched.         
	Calcutta: Coca-Cola India Tuesday announced the expanded Sprite Gully Cricket championship-season 2 to be played in Jamshedpur, Ranchi, Guwahati, Burdwan, Siliguri and Patna along with Calcutta. The winners will get an opportunity to meet Shah Rukh Khan, Sourav Ganguly and other members of the Kolkata Knight Riders along with a cash award of Rs 3 lakh.         
	New Delhi: Hockey India said Tuesday that it was trying to put in place a gradation system before the World Cup, that begins here on February 28, after meeting the captains and coaches of the national teams.         
	Mumbai: Former 1500m national record holder Eddie Sequeira, who participated in the 1972 Munich Games, is recuperating in a hospital after sustaining burn injuries in Goa a few days ago.        
	Arizona: Jeev Milkha Singh will take on three-time Major winner Padraig Harrington in the first round of the WGC-Accenture Match Play Championship at the Ritz-Carlton Golf Club Wednesday.
                                                                                                                                                      
